##############################################

DOCUMENT();

loadMacros(
  "PGstandard.pl",
  "MathObjects.pl",
  "PGML.pl",
  "contextFraction.pl",
  "PGcourse.pl",
);

##############################################

Context("Numeric");

# the base
$a = random(2,4,1)*(-1);

# numerator
$b = (random(1.5,9.5)+0.5)*random(-1,1,2);

# the exponent
$n = random(2,3,1);


Context("LimitedFraction");
Context()->flags->set(showMixedNumbers=>0, requireProperFractions=>1);
$ans = Compute($b*($a)**$n);





##############################################
TEXT(beginproblem());

BEGIN_PGML
Rewrite the expression simplified and using only positive exponents.

    [`
        \displaystyle\frac{[$b]}{([$a])^{[$n*(-1)]}}=
     `][____________]{$ans}

 
 

END_PGML


BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION

We evaluate the expression by remembering that [`x^{-n}`] is the same thing as [``\frac{1}{x^n}``] 
for any non-zero,
real value of [`x`].
 
    [``
      \begin{aligned}
            \frac{[$b]}{([$a])^{[$n*(-1)]}} & = \frac{[$b]}{\frac{1}{([$a])^{[$n]}}}\\
                                    & = [$b]\cdot([$a])^{[$n]}\\
                             & = [$ans]
      \end{aligned}
    ``]

Remember that when we divide by a fraction we _multiply_ by its reciprocal.
END_PGML_SOLUTION
